This paper is about online planning under uncertainty for robotics, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and robotics (RO). The paper also discusses the use of parallel computing, which falls under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC). The paper proposes a new algorithm, which involves machine learning (LG) techniques such as Monte-Carlo simulations. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.DC.
